premise_source_doc_sentence: When growing the plant grows upright branches with red tinted green leafy stems which produce flower clusters that have the appearance of baby broccoli .

Kinwaqucha lies northeast of the village of Kinwa Khuchu  (  `` quinoa corner '' , also spelled Ccuenhuacucho  )  , also named Kinwa Wayq ' u  (  `` quinoa stream '' , Cenhuahuaycco  )  , and the small lake named Pukaqucha '  (  `` red lake '' , Pucacocha  )  .
The plant Chenopodium nuttalliae is closely related to Chenopodium quinoa from the Andes  (  known as quinoa  )  , but the seeds do not contain that much saponins as quinoa seed does .
Quinoa  (  -LSB- ˈkiːnwɑː -RSB- or -LSB- kɪˈnoʊ.ə -RSB- , from Quechua kinwa or kinuwa  )  is the common name for Chenopodium quinoa , a flowering plant in the amaranth family Amaranthaceae .
Prior to the development of maize by Native Americans southern Mexico , this plant was one of the major `` grain '' crops .
